Corona Avenue, west side, opposite Fifty-fourth Avenue, showing in 4 views the Shady Lake farmhouse demolished in October 1928. Some of the owners of this house were John H. Smith, 1852; and Mrs. E. A. Smith, 1850-1873. John H. Smith settled in Corona in 1837. He was married to Eliza Ann Shearwood. Part of this farm is now known as Corona Heights.

1922
Views 2 & 3: April 1923
View 4: May 1926

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
